player.difficulty: There was a couple of times when I tried to sell but was unable to click the sell button.    A suggestion for any future iterations of this study:    I don't know the full nature of your experiment, so this may be a bad suggestion buuut... It may be a good idea to obscure the exact percentages from the participants and instead say something like 'low' or 'high' chance of dropping to zero at each step.     The reasoning is the following. When I was, for example, given 2% (5%) probability, I would aim to sell the stock after 25 (10) iterations since this would give me a 50/50 chance of making money on each round. This seemed like a good strategy to balance the risk/award, but it is probably not very reflective of a real life scenario since you would never know these percentages. You would however be more likely to have an idea on whether the risk is high or low.
